    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@vvo Adwords retargeting are those ad blocks on websites that display products you recently viewed. To do that Google Adwords needs to know what products a customer viewed/searched for. \n\nTo do so we need to implement some code that runs after a search. That code needs to contain this info:\n\n```\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\nvar google_tag_params = {\necomm_prodid: \"REPLACE_WITH_STRING_VALUE\",\necomm_pagetype: \"REPLACE_WITH_STRING_VALUE\"\n};\n</script>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n/* <![CDATA[ */\nvar google_conversion_id = xxxxxxxx;\nvar google_custom_params = window.google_tag_params;\nvar google_remarketing_only = true;\n/* ]]> */\n</script>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"//www.googleadservices.com/pagead/conversion.js\">\n</script>\n<noscript>\n<div style=\"display:inline;\">\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" style=\"border-style:none;\" alt=\"\" src=\"//googleads.g.doubleclick.net/pagead/viewthroughconversion/xxxxxxxx/?value=0&guid=ON&script=0\"/>\n</div>\n</noscript>\n\n\n```\n\necomm_prodid is an array with the product id's as in the shopping feed\necomm_pagetype is a predefined string which is the same for all search queries on this page. \n\nSo the main thing is that the ecomm_prodid gets filled with the product id's after a search and that the listed code is executed.\n\nIs this clear enough? Or do you have additional questions?\n",
