    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ok then to do so, you could do a small custom widget like this:\n\n``` js\nvar adWidget = {\n  render: function(params) {\n    var ids = params.results.hits.map(function(hit) { return hit.id });\n    adWordsCallWith(ids);\n  }\n};\n\nsearch.addWidget(adWidget);\n```\n\nSomething like that would work, then about the calls to make to google adwords, its up to you. There I cannot really help you.\n\nLet me know how it goes.\n",
